--[ 1 - Introduction

The purpose of this document is to guide both the implementation and
inspection of the Interfere plugin.


--[ 2 - Datastructures

There are exactly two datastructures that define the state of an Interfere
instance at any time:

 - the global configuration
 - the instance configuration


----[ 2.1.1 - Global configuration

The global configuration is the same for every plugin instance. This
includes settings regarding the sound quality and presets.


----[ 2.1.2 - Instance configuration

The instance configuration can differ among plugin instances. For example,
if specific components are turned on or off and what waveforms are loaded.


------[ 2.1.2.1 - Parameter matrix

The can be fully represented as a matrix, with the rows representing the
dependent variables, the columns the dependent variables, and the cells the
weights.

		Base value	Env 1		Env 2		...
===========================================================================
Osc. A. vol. 	1.0		-0.2		0.0  		...
Osc. B. vol. 	0.5		-0.93		0.1  		...
...		...		...		...		...


